[[[description]]]
Argument information for built-in functions is important for the sake of the reflection API.

The `ZEND_ARG_ARRAY_INFO` macro is used to specify the argument is an array.

[[[additional_information]]]
This macro only exists because it predates `ZEND_ARG_TYPE_INFO`, which can also be used to specify the argument is an array.

### Example

    ZEND_BEGIN_ARG_WITH_RETURN_TYPE_INFO_EX(arginfo_array_walk, 0, 2, _IS_BOOL, 0)
        ZEND_ARG_ARRAY_INFO(1, array, 0) // passed by reference
        ZEND_ARG_CALLABLE_INFO(0, callback, 0)
    ZEND_END_ARG_INFO()
